This is libctl, a Guile-based library for supporting flexible control
files in scientific simulations.  libctl is copyright (c) 1998 by
Steven G. Johnson.

Before using libctl, you should first run the configure script:

./configure

Documentation can be found in the doc/ directory, and an example
program in the examples/ directory.  The main source code for libctl
is in the src/ and utils/ directories.

In utils/libgeom, you can find specification files and functions
for dealing with structures consisting of solid geometric objects
in some lattice basis.  The example program uses this code.

